<h1> 15% OFF Wine Desks! </h1><h2><a href="buy-ninja-standing-desk.html" style="color:red;font-weight:bold">Drunken Ninja Back to School/Fall Sale!  <br /> Don't Wait, Ninjas sober up quick - Sale Ends Soon! </a> </h2>
<h2>The Ninja Standing Desk is the world's first portable sit and stand desk. </h2>


<p>The compact, lightweight design is perfect for travelers, contractors, and anyone who is tight on space. Finally there's a fully adjustable standing desk at a price you can afford!</p>

<p>Other standing desks on the market are hundreds to thousands of dollars!  </p>


<p>The Ninja Standing Desk hangs from a door, wall, or cubicle and is available in 2- and 3-shelf models. It can hold a laptop, monitor, keyboard, and mouse combination as preferred. By adding a third shelf it can also be used as a sitting desk by simply moving the laptop and keyboard down one shelf, and pulling a chair up to the desk.
The desk is adjustable to any height and tilt angle; it folds up into a compact package for easy transport, and is sturdy enough for everyday use!</p>

<p><blockquote><i>"Using the Ninja Standing Desk, I was more focused and productive and even lost weight from burning extra calories by standing up. I was assassinating my deadlines, slicing through my work day, while feeling healthier and nimble as a ninja."</i></blockquote></p>


<p><blockquote><i>"When I was a kid I dreamed of growing up to become a ninja. Now poor computer working ergonomics won’t keep me from that very dream!" says inventor Dan McDonley.</i></blockquote></p>

<ul>
<b>Specs</b>
<li>Length: 26”</li>
<li>Depth: 11”</li>
<li>Height: Infinite adjustability</li>
<li>Weight: 2-shelf model weighs less than 5 lbs</li>
<li>Folded Dimensions: 3" x 11" x 13"</li>
<li>Load: Each shelf is rated individually for 30 lbs and the entire desk is rated for 80 lbs</li>
<li>Colors: Black or wine shelves with silver straps</li>
<li>Supports: T9 Military grade anodized aluminum tubing with shock cord</li>
</ul>


<h3>Designed and built at the <a href="http://techshop.ws">TechShop</a> in San Francisco.
Manufactured entirely in the USA - mainly in the San Francisco Bay Area</h3>


<p>Folding up to about the size of a thick laptop, the Ninja Standing Desk fits easily into a laptop bag, backpack, or carry-on luggage, and weighs about 4 lbs. It takes only minutes to set up, and provides the <b>freedom to work anywhere</b> there is a place to hang it from. With T9 military grade aluminum support poles, the desk is rated for 30 lbs per shelf and 80 lbs total: strong enough to hold any computer workstation.</p>



